  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — Singleton registration; no extra abstraction layers, no factories.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — leaf executor only; do not introduce new public types beyond the executor class itself.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — verify publish-size delta at end of task (expected: minimal increase, well under +2 MB NFR-01).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — unit tests follow in tasks 007-009. This task's "compiles" gate satisfies the build-clean precondition.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">New component justification triple:
      1. Existing: AiAnalysisNodeExecutor exists but requires Tool + Document — wrong contract for prompt-only calls (R4 /narrate failed because of this).
      2. Extension: cannot extend AiAnalysisNodeExecutor without breaking its existing contract (it's used by Insights pipeline). New executor is required.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: R4 /narrate cannot ship; ExecutorType.AiCompletion = 1 enum value remains unimplemented; "prompt-only LLM call" workflow remains impossible in the platform.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist applies. Placement decision: keep IN BFF — AiCompletionNodeExecutor is a leaf executor in the existing Services/Ai/Nodes/ pattern, NOT a new AI surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F.1">Asymmetric-Registration Tier 1.5 Anti-Pattern — this executor is registered unconditionally (not behind a feature flag), so no Null-Object pattern needed.</constraint>
  </constraints>

